> New to gochujang sauce? This colorful stir-fry is the perfect introduction! Gochujang is
> a Korean paste made from chili peppers—so as you can imagine, a little goes a long way!
> We sweeten it up here with sesame dressing, add a dash of Sriracha for tang, then use it to
> coat browned turkey with broccoli, cauliflower, and carrots. Ponzu rice and pickled cabbage
> are the perfect sides to mellow out all those punchy flavors... and there you have it. Nice
> to meet you, gochujang!

In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup} (1 1/2 cups for 4
servings), and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low. Cook, covered,
until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

In a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @Rice Wine Vinegar{5%teaspoon}, @Sugar{1%tsp}
(2 tsp for 4), @water{2%TBSP} (4 TBSP for 4), and a big pinch of @salt{}. Whisk until sugar
and salt have dissolved. Microwave for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @Shredded Red Cabbage{4%ounce}. Set aside to pickle, stirring occasionally.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Soy Sauce{2%tablespoon}, @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon},
@Cornstarch{1%tablespoon}, and @water{1/4%cup} (1/3 cup for 4 servings). Whisk until no
lumps remain.

Stir in @Gochujang Sauce{1%ounce}, @Sesame Dressing{1.5%ounce}, and @Sriracha{1%teaspoon}
(use less if you prefer less heat) until combined.

Cut @Broccoli, Cauliflower, and Carrot Blend{6%ounce} into bite-size pieces if necessary.

Place broccoli, cauliflower, and carrots in a second medium microwave-safe bowl{};
cover bowl with #plastic wrap{}. Microwave until tender, ~{2%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add @Ground Turkey{10%ounce} and season with @salt{1/4%tsp} (1/2 tsp for 4
servings). Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and almost cooked through,
~{3-5%minutes}.

Stir in sauce and broccoli, cauliflower, and carrots. Cook, stirring, until sauce has
thickened and turkey is cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}. Stir in @Ponzu Sauce{6%milliliters} and @Butter{1%tablespoon}
(2 TBSP for 4 servings); season with @salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Divide rice, stir-fry, and pickled cabbage (draining first) between bowls. Sprinkle with
@Sesame Seeds{1%tablespoon} and serve.